<div class="section_title">CES Celebrates 40 years!</div>
<span class="text">
<IMG hspace=5 src="/images/general/CES_40anv125.gif" align=right>The International CES marks its <A href="/attendees/special_events/3840.asp">40th anniversary</A> this year, and here's what you need to know to make sure you don't miss any of the fun:
<UL>
<LI><A href="/attendees/special_events/default.asp">40th Anniversary Party<BR></A>&nbsp;ESPN/CEA Stage in the LVCC, Grand Lobby<BR>Noon on Monday, January 8, 2007, to join in the festivities at our very own CES celebration! Elvis Presley and Marilyn Monroe have already sent in their RSVPs. There will be plenty of sweets and commemorative gifts.<BR></LI>
<LI><A href="/attendees/special_events/3840.asp">Inaugural Exhibitors: 1967</A><BR>CES would like to acknowledge the following exhibitors who exhibited at the very first CES in New York City in 1967 and are exhibiting again in 2007. Is your company on the list? <A href="/attendees/special_events/3840.asp">Look here.</A><BR></LI>
<LI><A href="/attendees/default_flash.asp">40-day Countdown to the 2007 International CES</A><BR>Fact #40: The first CES took place in New York City, June 25 to 28, 1967, at the Americana and the New York Hilton hotels. The program hosted 17,500 attendees and 110 exhibitors in 150,000 square feet of exhibit space. That same month, the first automatic cash machine was installed in England. <A href="/attendees/default_flash.asp">See more facts as we draw closer to&nbsp;opening day.</A>&nbsp;<BR></LI>
<LI><A href="/attendees/special_events/3840.asp">How Many Times Have You Attended CES?</A><BR>We know CES has been around for 40 years, but we want to acknowledge all of our loyal attendees who have been coming to the show over the years. Pick up your special CES ribbon at t a variety of locations. <A href="/attendees/special_events/3840.asp">More.</A></LI></UL>
