<div class="section_title">Official Show Publications</div>
<span class="text">
We recently received some questions regarding the <A href="/exhibitors/promotions/print.asp">official show publications</A> for the International CES, and we wanted to be sure and clear up any confusion for you. 
<P>There are six official publications for the 2007 International CES. Each of these publications, listed below, is produced for us by one of several of our key media partners. These are the only publications and show dailies that are endorsed by and produced at the request of the International CES. </P>
<OL type=1>
<LI><EM>Pre-Show Planner</EM>, produced by the Consumer Technology Publishing Group </LI>
<LI><EM>Show Guide</EM>, produced by the Consumer Technology Publishing Group </LI>
<LI><EM>Directory</EM>, produced by the Consumer Technology Publishing Group </LI>
<LI><EM>Addendum</EM>, produced by the Consumer Technology Publishing Group </LI>
<LI><EM>CES Show Daily</EM>, produced by TWICE </LI>
<LI><EM>CES Mobile Daily</EM>, produced by CMP</LI></OL>
<P>Please note: The <EM>Consumer Electronics Daily News </EM>is <STRONG>not </STRONG>an official show publication. We do realize that many of you have received calls or solicitations from this company stating they are one of our partners. This publication is not created at the request of the International CES, nor is it distributed on-site at the show with the rest of the show publications.<BR>&nbsp;<BR>Get more information on our <A href="/exhibitors/promotions/print.asp">official show publications</A>.</P>
