<div class="section_title">Expand Into International Markets with Show Time at CES</div>
<span class="text">
U.S. Department of Commerce's Commercial Service, CS, will run their Show Time program at the 2007 International CES. <BR><BR>This program provides U.S. exhibitors an opportunity to meet with CS Consumer Electronics Industry Specialists from U.S. Embassies around the world and receive customized export counseling to discuss selected markets including doing business in that market, how to find contacts, market research, and standards requirements.
<UL>
<LI>Explore international sales opportunities. </LI>
<LI>Grow your international sales. </LI>
<LI>Discover new markets where your products may succeed. </LI>
<LI>Fine-tune your international sales strategy by discussing specifics with country specialists in one-on-one appointments.</LI></UL>
<P>For more information, visit <A href="http://www.buyusa.gov/ict/ces2007showtime" target=_blank>buyusa.gov</A>, e-mail <A href="mailto:Jennifer.Harrington@mail.doc.gov">Jennifer Harrington</A> or call (202) 482-0595.<BR><BR>Traveling from outside the U.S.? Visit our <A href="/international/default_flash.asp">international section</A>.</P>
