<div class="section_title">And the Emmy Goes To...CES</div>
<span class="text">
<IMG hspace=5 src="/images/general/Emmys-statuette.gif" align=right>The Technology &amp; Engineering Emmy® Awards will be CES’s opening evening event on Monday, January 8, 2007. To mark the first time the coveted Emmy Awards will be presented at CES, a gala event at The Venetian (6 p.m. reception, 7 p.m. dinner) is in the works. Receiving the Lifetime Achievement Award that evening will be Eddy Hartenstein, former Vice Chairman, The DIRECTV Group, Inc., who built DIRECTV from its inception into a world class provider of digital television entertainment as well as directed Hughes Communications’ expansion in commercial satellites supporting the broadcast and cable industries.&nbsp; 
<P>The Emmy Awards will honor technical achievements in two areas: Science &amp; Technology for Television and secondly, Advanced Media Technology encompassing interactive television and for the first time, the Internet, cell phones, private networks, and personal media players. Among the companies to receive Emmy Awards are Adobe, Apple, Gennum Corporation, Microsoft, RCA, RealNetworks, Terayon Communications Systems, Visible World, The Weather Channel, and posthumously Rene Anselmo, founder of PanAmSat. Additional honorees will be announced from the stellar group of nominees in Advance Media Technology categories.</P>
<P>“The International CES has long been the launch pad of entertainment technology,” said Peter Price, President/CEO, National Television Academy, “so it is fitting that our Technology &amp; Engineering Emmy Awards, which recognize achievement in both television engineering and advanced media technology be showcased there.”</P>
<P>For tickets and event information, contact Jessica York at <A href="mailto:rsvp@emmyonline.tv">rsvp@emmyonline.tv</A> or (212) 484-9440. For sponsorship opportunities, contact Sheryl Katz at <A href="mailto:skatz@emmyonline.tv">skatz@emmyonline.tv</A> or (212) 484-9436. See more about this and other <A href="/attendees/special_events/default.asp">special events</A> scheduled for CES.</P>
</span>
