<div class="section_title">HD Content From Disney Companies Available For CES Exhibitors’ Use</div>
<span class="text">
ESPN HD and ESPN2 HD will again offer a 20-minute footage tape for use on the floor at the 2007 International CES. 
<P>As a part of The Walt Disney Company involvement, this year’s effort will include expanded content from the ABC Television Network and Buena Vista Home Entertainment in addition to ESPN HD and ESPN2 HD. This content will include exciting sports footage from ESPN HD, ABC footage from Desperate Housewives, The View, Grey’s Anatomy and Good Morning America, plus Cars and Pirates of the Caribbean from Buena Vista Home Entertainment.&nbsp; </P>
<P>There will be no charge for this footage tape. In consideration for its availability, ESPN will only require its frequent use in a predominant position in each exhibitor’s space at the CES, including display on at least five screens by exhibitors with ten or more screens within its area. No editing of the footage or perceived endorsement of exhibitors’ products will be allowed. The footage will be shipped to exhibitors during the second week of December on 720 progressive scan D5 tape. Each exhibitor will be required to execute a release form before the footage will be released.</P>
<P>If you are interested please contact Cynthia Upson at <A href="mailto:cupson@CE.org">cupson@CE.org</A> or (804) 249-4865.</P>
</span>
